   {:e #blake3 "19cb976809f07d7bb93a080f60aaddc8dda408e04dbce9b7dae1643737bdaf74" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Policy manifest defines boundary weights (coverage, depth, coherence, completeness, formality). These weights are bootstrap defaults — never calibrated from empirical data. The hypothesis ledger computes prediction errors that SHOULD feed back into boundary weight adjustment. RATIONALE: ADR-FOUNDATION-024 (self-calibrating attention). Without calibrated weights, F(S) measures alignment against an arbitrary model. The hypothesis error data tells us which boundaries are well-predicted (accurate weights) vs poorly-predicted (need adjustment). APPROACH: (1) After HL-CLOSE-1 provides at least 3 data points, compute per-boundary prediction error. (2) Boundaries with high error get weight adjustment: increase weight for under-predicted, decrease for over-predicted. (3) Implementation: add calibrate_boundary_weights(store, hypothesis_outcomes) -> Vec<WeightAdjustment> to policy.rs. (4) Apply adjustments via policy manifest update transaction. ACCEPTANCE: (A) After calibration, boundary weights differ from bootstrap defaults. (B) Subsequent predictions have lower mean error (convergence). (C) F(S) computation reflects calibrated weights. DEPENDS-ON: HL-CLOSE-1 (need outcome data). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/policy.rs" :op :assert}
